AIM:
To design a simple Student Registration Form using HTML and connect it with a MySQL database using PHP.The form data is stored in the database and retrieved using the SQL SELECT query.

PROCEDURE:
Open MySQL Workbench and create the database studentdb.
Create the table students with fields: id, name, email.
Create the HTML form (index.html) for student registration.
Create insert.php to connect with MySQL and insert the submitted data.
Create view.php to retrieve and display stored records using SELECT * FROM students;.
Start Apache and MySQL using XAMPP/WAMP.
Open the form in the browser and enter data.
Check the database and view.php to confirm successful insertion and retrieval.

code:
1)Database:
CREATE DATABASE studentdb;

USE studentdb;

CREATE TABLE students (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    email VARCHAR(100)
);

2)index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Student Registration</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Student Registration Form</h2>

<form action="insert.php" method="post">
    Name: <input type="text" name="name" required><br><br>
    Email: <input type="email" name="email" required><br><br>

    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

<br>
<a href="view.php">View Students</a>

</body>
</html>

3)insert.php
<?php

$conn = mysqli_connect("localhost", "root", "Jeevaakash123@", "studentdb");

$name = $_POST['name'];
$email = $_POST['email'];

$sql = "INSERT INTO students (name, email) VALUES ('$name', '$email')";

if (mysqli_query($conn, $sql)) {
    echo "Record Inserted Successfully!<br><br>";
    echo "<a href='view.php'>View Students</a>";
} else {
    echo "Error: " . mysqli_error($conn);
}

mysqli_close($conn);
?>

4)view.php
<?php

$conn = mysqli_connect("localhost", "root", "Jeevaakash123@", "studentdb");

$result = mysqli_query($conn, "SELECT * FROM students");

echo "<h2>Registered Students</h2>";
echo "<table border='1' cellpadding='10'>
<tr>
    <th>ID</th>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Email</th>
</tr>";

while ($row = mysqli_fetch_assoc($result)) {
    echo "<tr>
            <td>".$row['id']."</td>
            <td>".$row['name']."</td>
            <td>".$row['email']."</td>
          </tr>";
}

echo "</table>";

mysqli_close($conn);
?>

RESULT:
Thus, the Student Registration Form was successfully created using HTML and PHP.The entered student data was stored in the MySQL database table and retrieved using the SQL SELECT query.
